{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"094c675f-a569-4d68-9996-6ff4f8d996e4","content":"No files found in the working directory. I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is the `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute. This tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, enabling compile-time resolution of all `{Binding …}` expressions.\n\n**2. Catch binding errors at build time** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat invalid compiled bindings as build errors -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith this enabled, a typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **compiler error** (e.g., *CS0117: 'SettingsViewModel' does not contain a definition for 'Themee'*) instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n**Key rules to remember:**\n- Every `{Binding}` under an `x:DataType` scope is compiled — misspelled or missing properties fail the build.\n- If a child element binds to a **different** type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`), set `x:DataType` on that element too.\n- To opt out for a specific binding (e.g., binding to the page itself), use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` locally or switch to `{Binding Source=…}`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b18be82d-6840-4565-8d67-8d1ac63996b4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking about converting a page conceptually. Let me provide the guidance directly since there are no actual files to modify.","outputTokens":713},"id":"2b9c505d-9c7e-480b-9015-61fd708a8319","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:59:13.679Z","parentId":"cb1471e6-0ca1-414a-88bc-fee3463f6ed6"}
